  "body": "### Component\n\nCast\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (6cd6618 2022-08-10T22:34:19.67820721Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\ncast run -v 0x2d951c5c95d374263ca99ad9c20c9797fc714330a8037429a3aa4c83d456f845\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThe cast command `cast run -v 0x2d951c5c95d374263ca99ad9c20c9797fc714330a8037429a3aa4c83d456f845` shows a transaction that immediately reverts.\r\n\r\nWhereas it didn't revert on mainnet:\r\nhttps://etherscan.io/tx/0x2d951c5c95d374263ca99ad9c20c9797fc714330a8037429a3aa4c83d456f845\r\n\r\nI think this is due to the transaction using the BASEFEE opcode and reverting because it's not correct. Could cast be using the BASEFEE of the previous block?",
